title: Iowa roundup: Volleyball, field hockey, soccer all drop matches
text:
Buy Photo Hawkeyes (Photo: The Register) Buy Photo
The Iowa volleyball team lost 3-0 to No. 16 Wisconsin Friday night in Carver-Hawkeye Arena in Iowa City. The Hawkeyes (10-12, 0-9 Big Ten) fell to the Badgers (13-6, 5-4) 22-25, 22-25, 18-25.
Iowa is winless since Sept. 19.
Lauren Brobst paced the Black and Gold offensively on Friday with 11 kills. Loxley Keala led the team in assists with 27, while Annika Olsen made 22 digs. Mikaela Gunderson had three blocks. Reagan Davey added six kills and 12 digs.
Iowa returns to action at 7 p.m. Saturday against No. 9 Minnesota in Iowa City.
•FIELD HOCKEY: Iowa lost 3-2 to Penn State in University Park, Pa. Penn State scored with no time remaining to secure the victory.
Iowa (9-8. 2-5 Big Ten) trailed 2-0 at halftime, but stormed back to tie the contest with the Nittany Lions (7-9, 3-4). Isabella Brown put the Hawkeyes on the scoreboard with a goal in the 37th minute and was followed by Stephanie Norlander’s score in the 52nd minute.
Penn State, however, notched a walk-off goal with a score via a penalty corner shot with no time left.
•SOCCER: Iowa dropped a match to Nebraska 5-3 at the Iowa Soccer Complex in Iowa City.
The Hawkeyes (7-9-1, 1-8-1) led 2-1 at one stage, but Nebraska (7-7-2, 3-5-2) scored three unanswered goals to stake out a 4-2 lead. Iowa notched a goal to narrow the deficit to 4-3, but the Cornhuskers added a fifth goal late in the match to seal the win.
Karly Stuenkel scored two goals for Iowa, while Hannah Kousheh added another. Bri Toelle had an assist.
Iowa was outshot 18-9.
